Response to Claude items:

- Item 1, time-stop overshoot: accept Claude's advice. No code change.
  In a bar-driven backtest, exiting at the first available bar close after a
  missing time-stop bar is the least surprising behavior. An open-fill special
  case would change the fill model.
- Item 2, M4 multi-contract pre-filter: agree. For this RTH-only parent,
  RTH pre-filtering before `prepare_bars(...)` is intentional input scoping,
  not a loader defect. A legitimate future ETH strategy would need its own
  session/contract policy before calling the strict loader.
- Item 3, M3 VWAP target: agree to fix the look-ahead, but not with the entry
  bar's full-bar VWAP. At an entry-bar open, the entry bar's full OHLC/volume
  VWAP is not observable. I implemented a fixed target using the closed signal
  bar's `SessionVWAP`, which is causal at entry.
- Item 4, signal-to-entry gap: already fixed in `37ffd9d`.

